ThinkPart(
    type='think',
    think='Let me check a few more critical things:\n\n1. The `city` mode in `ma
tching.service.ts` uses 50km just like `nearby`, but PRD says "同城市，根据用户
当前位置行政边界".\n2. The `avatar_url` in `RecommendationCardDto` is optional (
`@IsOptional()`) but OpenAPI and generated mobile models require it. This could 
cause deserialization errors.\n3. Socket.io client integration is completely mis
sing in mobile despite having `socket_io_client` in pubspec and `ExternalMatchRe
ceived` event in bloc.\n4. No widget tests for matching components.\n5. No bloc 
tests for `MatchingBloc` or `MatchListCubit`.\n6. `HomePage` uses its own `_Card
StackArea` instead of the design system `SwipeCardStack` - duplicated logic.\n7.
The `MatchingBloc` has a state `MatchingSwipeInProgress` but when the swipe API 
fails, it transitions to `MatchingFailure` instead of reverting to the previous 
card state.\n8. In `matching.service.ts`, when `recordAction` encounters a dupli
cate entry (`ER_DUP_ENTRY`) for a `like` action, it checks for existing match bu
t doesn\'t return `conversationId` or `matchedUser` for the existing match - onl
y `matchId`.\n9. The `MatchingGateway.handleConnection` joins the room, but I ne
ed to check if there\'s any socket event handling in mobile.\n10. In `matching.s
ervice.ts` line 103: `mode === "nationwide" ? 99999 : mode === "city" ? 50 : 50;
` - city and nearby both use 50km. This doesn\'t match PRD requirements for city
mode.\n11. The `MatchingBloc._onSwipeActionSubmitted` removes the card from UI b
efore the API call succeeds (optimistic update). If the API fails, the card is a
lready gone and user sees an error. This is a UX issue.\n12. Check if `recommend
ations:{user_id}:{mode}` cache key is correct - yes, it includes mode.\n13. Chec
k if there\'s any missing `ProfileCompletionGuard` on `MatchesController` - the 
`MatchesController` only has `JwtAuthGuard`, not `ProfileCompletionGuard`. Is th
is intentional? The PRD says users need complete profile for matching features.\
n14. The `MatchingController` injects `MatchingGateway` but `MatchingGateway` is
also provided in `MatchingModule`. This is fine.\n15. Check the `MatchingBloc` s
tate transition from `MatchingMatchCreated` to `MatchingLoadEmpty` or `MatchingL
oadSuccess` - it happens on `MatchModalDismissed`. But what about `ExternalMatch
Received`? It transitions to `MatchingMatchCreated` without `previousCards`, so 
if user dismisses the modal, it would go to empty state. That\'s acceptable sinc
e it\'s an external notification.\n16. The `MatchListPage` doesn\'t handle pagin
ation properly - it just shows a loading indicator at the bottom but never actua
lly fetches more.\n17. The `docs/api/matching.md` says error code `1001` for pro
file incomplete, but the API returns `1000` with HTTP 400 in `matching.service.t
s` line 87-92. This is an inconsistency between docs and code.\n\nLet me check o
ne more thing about the `city` mode and the `SwipeActionDto`.',
    encrypted=None
)
